b'II. How to Apply'
b'A. Admission Requirements'
b'Mechanical Engineering'
b'MS Thesis/Non-Thesis'
b'In addition to the Graduate College minimum requirements, applicants must meet the following program requirements: Baccalaureate Field:'
b'Graduate College'
b'Mechanical engineering. The degree must be from an American Board of Engineering Technology (ABET) accredited college or university or equivalent.'
b'Grade Point Average:'
b'At least 3.00/4.00 for the final 60 semester hours (90 quarter hours) of undergraduate study. A grade point average of at least 3.50 is preferred for applicants to the PhD program.'
b'Tests Required:'
b'International applicants are required to take the GRE. Applicants seeking a teaching or research assistantship are strongly encouraged to take the GRE General.'
b'Minimum English Competency Test Score: TOEFL:'
b'550 (paper-based); 80, with subscores of Reading 19, Listening 17, Speaking 20, and Writing 21 (iBT Internet-based), OR,'
b'IELTS:'
b'6.5, with subscores of 6.0 for all four subscores, OR,'
b'PTE-Academic:'
b'54, with subscores of Reading 51, Listening 47, Speaking 53, and Writing 56.'
b'Letters of Recommendation:'
b'Three required.'
b'Personal Statement:'
b'Required.'
b'Other Requirements:'
b'Admission to the PhD program is not automatic for students completing their MS degree in the department. Master\xe2\x80\x99s students who desire to continue on to the PhD must see the department\xe2\x80\x99s graduate coordinator for forms to apply to the PhD program.'
b'Nondegree Applicants:'
b'Nondegree applicants may be admitted for no more than 8 semester hours.'
